		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Jayson Blair</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p><b>Jayson Blair</b> (born <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1976-03-23"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="03-23"><a href="/wiki/March_23" title="March 23">March 23</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1976" title="1976">1976</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/Columbia,_Maryland" title="Columbia, Maryland">Columbia, Maryland</a>) is a journalist who resigned from the <i><a href="/wiki/New_York_Times" title="New York Times" class="mw-redirect">New York Times</a></i> in May 2003, after he was caught <a href="/wiki/Plagiarism" title="Plagiarism">plagiarizing</a> and fabricating elements of his stories.</p>
<table id="toc" class="toc" summary="Contents">
