<p><a name="Cultural_references" id="Cultural_references"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Jayson_Blair&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7" title="Edit section: Cultural references">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Cultural references</span></h2>
<p>Season 5 of the HBO series <i><a href="/wiki/The_Wire" title="The Wire">The Wire</a></i>, which is set in Baltimore, dealt with this subject and others relating to journalism and the print media business.</p>
<p>A scene in <i><a href="/wiki/Gilmore_Girls" title="Gilmore Girls">Gilmore Girls</a></i> episode "The Reigning Lorelai" (4.16) shows Rory's editor, Doyle, becoming frustrated with the way Yale Daily News staffers act in the newsroom calling it "the breeding ground for the next Jayson Blair."</p>
<p>The plot of <i><a href="/wiki/Law_%26_Order:_Criminal_Intent" title="Law &amp; Order: Criminal Intent">Law &amp; Order: Criminal Intent</a></i> episode "<a href="/wiki/Pravda_(Law_%26_Order:_Criminal_Intent_episode)" title="Pravda (Law &amp; Order: Criminal Intent episode)">Pravda</a>" (3.5) resembles the Jayson Blair scandal.</p>
